gomodel:SYNGO_5272  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1b: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Cbl-b and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured spinal cord dorsal horn neurons showed partial co-localization. Imaging resolution was too low to pinpoint precise synaptic localization.\n\nFigure 2: Cbl-b specifically interacts with NMDAR subunit GluN2B (GRIN2B) in co-immunoprecipitations from spinal cord dorsal horn of adult mice and HEK293T cells.\n\nFigure 3: Cbl-b enhanced the ubiquitination and reduced the surface expression of GluN2B in spinal neuron cultures and HEK293T cells.\n\nFigure 4: Cbl-b promotes the developmental decline of synaptic GluN2B receptors.. Experimental description: M&M: \"The primary neurons were cultured as described previously (26). Briefly, the mouse pups (P1) were decapitated, and the dorsal quadrants of spinal cords were dissected into ice-cold Hanks' balanced salt solution (HBSS) supplemented with 10 mM Hepes.\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit anti-Cbl-b antibody (Proteintech, Rosemont, IL, USA)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5272" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

